ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsweetened cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "confectioners' sugar"}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour an 8-inch square pan.. Melt 1/2 cup butter in a large saucepan. Remove from heat, and stir in sugar, eggs, and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat in 1/3 cup cocoa, flour, salt, and baking powder. Spread batter into prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until top is dry and edges have started to pull away from the sides of the pan, about 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool briefly before frosting.. To make the frosting: Combine softened butter, confectioners' sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa, honey, and 1 teaspoon vanilla extract in a bowl. Stir until smooth. Frost brownies while they are still warm.

steps: Gather all ingredients.. Season salmon fillets with lemon pepper, garlic powder, and salt.. name: Jen's Hearty Three Meat Chili

steps: Cook and stir sausage in a large skillet over medium heat until browned. Drain; place sausage in a pot large enough to hold all ingredients. In same skillet, cook and stir onion with ground beef over medium heat until beef is browned and onions are tender; drain and add to the large pot.. In same skillet, cook and stir stew beef over medium heat until browned. Without draining, pour stew beef into the large pot.. Pour tomatoes, beer, and water into the pot with meats. Stir in chili powder, red pepper, white pepper, sugar, and cinnamon. Season to taste with salt and black pepper. Simmer until stew beef is very tender, at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally and adding more water as needed. If you prefer a thicker chili, thicken as needed with tomato paste. If using kidney beans, add them 10 minutes before serving, just in time to heat through.

steps: Gather all ingredients.. Heat a large stock pot over medium-high heat. Crumble ground chuck and sausage into the hot pan. Cook, stirring frequently, until meat is evenly browned. Drain off excess grease.. Pour in chili beans, spicy chili beans, diced tomatoes, and tomato paste. Add celery, onion, bell peppers, chile peppers, bacon bits, bouillon, beer, 1/4 cup chili powder, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, oregano, cumin, hot pepper sauce, basil, cayenne, paprika, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1 teaspoon black pepper. steps: Gather all ingredients.. Transfer potato slices to a large bowl of cold water as you slice them.. Drain slices and rinse under cold water. Refill the bowl with water, add 3 tablespoons salt, and put slices back in the bowl. Let potatoes soak in the salty water for at least 30 minutes.. Drain and rinse slices again. Pat dry.. Heat oil in a deep-fryer to 365 degrees F (185 degrees C).. Working in small batches, fry potato slices until golden. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. steps: Place beef in a skillet over medium heat and cook until evenly brown, 8 to 10 minutes. Drain grease.. Shake the curds a time or two to remove excess batter.. Deep fry curds in hot oil until golden brown, 1 or 2 minutes. Drain on paper towels; serve hot.

ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'chicken wings, tips discarded'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper, more to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey, divided'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'hot sauce'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill to medium heat and lightly oil the grate.. Pat wings dry with paper towels. Season wings with cayenne, salt, and pepper.. Cook chicken wings on the preheated grill, brushing wings liberally with 1/2 cup honey while cooking, until cooked through and juices run clear, 20 to 30 minutes.. Mix butter, hot sauce, and remaining 1/2 cup honey together in a large bowl.. Remove wings from the grill and immediately toss them in hot honey-butter sauce to coat. Serve wings or return to the grill for 1 minute per side to set sauce.

name: Pumpkin Cupcakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground allspice'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pumpkin puree'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': "confectioners' sugar"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}
steps: Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease 24 muffin cups or line cups with paper liners.. To make the pumpkin cupcakes: Sift flour, baking powder, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, cloves, allspice, baking soda, and salt together in a large bowl; set aside.. Beat white sugar, ½ cup butter, and brown sugar together in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add pumpkin puree and milk; stir in flour mixture until just combined. Spoon batter into the prepared muffin cups, filling each 3/4 full.. Bake in the preheated oven until tops spring back when lightly pressed, about 25 minutes. Cool in the pans for 5 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack and let cool, about 20 minutes.. To make the frosting: Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup butter together in a large bowl with an electric mixer until smooth. Beat in confectioners' sugar, a little at a time, until incorporated. Add vanilla extract and 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon; beat until fluffy.. Frost cooled cupcakes.

name: Fried Mac and Cheese Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(7.25 ounce) package', 'name': 'macaroni and cheese mix'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pimento cheese spread'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Italian cheese blend'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'peanut oil for frying, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'Italian seasoned bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'milk'}
steps: Gather the ingredients.. Fill a pot with lightly salted water and bring to a rolling boil over high heat. Stir in macaroni, and return to a boil. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally until macaroni is cooked through but still firm to the bite, about 7 minutes. Drain. Stir in butter, 1/4 cup milk, and cheese packet from the macaroni and cheese package.. While macaroni is still hot, stir in Cheddar cheese, pimento cheese spread, and Italian cheese blend, and continue to stir until melted.. Place the macaroni and cheese mixture into a container and refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Remove the macaroni mixture from the refrigerator, and using a cookie scoop, scoop into balls. Place mac balls on the prepared baking sheet and freeze for at least 2 hours.. Heat oil in a deep fryer or large saucepan to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Make a breading station: Whisk bread crumbs with paprika, chili powder, black pepper, sugar, salt, and cayenne in a shallow dish; set aside. Beat eggs with 3 tablespoons milk in a small bowl. Remove the mac balls from the freezer, coat in egg mixture, and then dredge in breading.. Fry the mac balls in hot oil in small batches until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes. Drain briefly on a paper towel-lined plate; serve hot.

name: Blonde Brownies
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sifted all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'semisweet chocolate chips'}
steps: Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Grease a 9x9-inch baking pan.. Sift together sifted flour, baking powder, salt, and baking soda in a medium bowl. Stir in chopped nuts; set aside.. Mix brown sugar and melted butter in a large bowl until combined; cool slightly.. Stir beaten egg and vanilla into brown sugar mixture. Add flour mixture, a little at a time, mixing just until combined. Spread batter into the prepared baking pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.

name: Delicious Raspberry Oatmeal Cookie Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'seedless raspberry jam'}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease an 8x8-inch square pan; line with greased foil.. Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl. Rub in butter using your hands or a pastry blender to form a crumbly mixture.. Press 2 cups oat mixture into the bottom of the prepared pan.. Spread jam to within 1/4 inch of the edge.. Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top; press down lightly into jam.. Bake in the preheated oven until lightly browned, 35 to 40 minutes.. Allow to cool before cutting into bars.

name: Sweet Restaurant Slaw

name: Wisconsin Bratwurst
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'fresh bratwurst sausages'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '(12 fluid ounce) cans or bottles', 'name': 'beer'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onions, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': '', 'name': 'hoagie rolls'}
steps: Prick bratwurst with a fork to prevent them from exploding as they cook.. Place in a large stockpot. Add beer, onions, butter, and black pepper. Place the stockpot over medium heat, bring to a boil and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.. Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Cook bratwurst on the preheated grill until evenly browned, about 10 to 14 minutes, turning occasionally. Serve hot off the grill with onions on hoagie rolls.

name: Grill Master Chicken Wings
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'chicken wings, cut apart at joints, wing tips discarded'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Italian-style salad dressing'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "hot pepper sauce (such as Frank's RedHot), or to taste"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}
steps: Prepare wings: Combine chicken wings, soy sauce, and Italian dressing in a large resealable plastic bag; coat chicken wings with marinade, squeeze out excess air, and seal the bag. Marinate in the refrigerator, 4 hours to overnight.. Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Prepare sauce: Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat. Stir in hot pepper sauce and soy sauce until combined. Remove from heat and set aside.. Remove chicken wings from marinade and pat dry; discard any remaining marinade.. Cook on the preheated grill, turning occasionally, until chicken is browned and no longer pink, 25 to 30 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Place grilled wings in a large bowl. Pour butter sauce over wings; toss until well-coated.

name: It's Chili by George!!
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'lean ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(46 fluid ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(29 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'kidney beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'pinto beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cayenne pepper'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir ground beef in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain and discard grease.. Transfer browned beef into a large pot over medium heat; stir in tomato juice, tomato sauce, kidney beans, pinto beans, onions, bell pepper, chili powder, cumin, salt, sugar, oregano, ground black pepper, and cayenne pepper.. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

name: Baked Hawaiian Sandwiches
ingredients: {'quantity': '24', 'unit': '', 'name': "Hawaiian bread rolls (such as King's®), split"}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '', 'name': 'thin slices of honey-cured deli ham, halved'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'Swiss cheese, halved'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'thin slices', 'name': 'deli smoked turkey, halved'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'thin slices', 'name': 'provolone cheese, halved'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried onion flakes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'poppy seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'honey mustard'}
steps: Place a rack into lower half of the oven and preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Arrange bottom halves of Hawaiian rolls on a baking sheet. Place a half slice each of ham, Swiss cheese, smoked turkey, and provolone cheese onto each roll bottom. Place top halves onto each bottom to make sandwiches.. Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat; stir in sugar, dried onion flakes, poppy seeds, and honey mustard until mixture is smooth and sugar has dissolved, about 2 minutes; brush over the tops of each sandwich.. Bake sandwiches on the preheated oven's lower rack until tops are golden brown and fillings are hot, about 15 minutes.

name: Slow Cooker Vegan Chili
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onions, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'yellow bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) cans', 'name': 'diced tomatoes with juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'garbanzo beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'kidney beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(6 ounce) cans', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen chopped spinach, thawed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen corn kernels, thawed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'zucchini, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'yellow squash, chopped'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried parsley'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato sauce, or more if needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable broth, or more if needed'}
steps: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onions, bell peppers, and garlic; cook and stir until onions start to brown, 8 to 10 minutes.. Transfer mixture into a slow cooker. Stir in tomatoes, black beans, garbanzo beans, kidney beans, tomato paste, spinach, corn, zucchini, yellow squash, chili powder, cumin, oregano, parsley, salt, and pepper until thoroughly mixed.. Pour the tomato sauce and vegetable broth over the ingredients. Cook on Low for 4 to 5 hours. Check seasoning. If chili is too thick, add more tomato sauce and vegetable broth to desired thickness. Cook on Low for an additional 1 to 2 hours.

name: Slow Cooker Carolina BBQ
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5 pound)', 'name': 'bone-in pork shoulder roast'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'hot pepper sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}
steps: Place pork shoulder into a slow cooker and season with salt and pepper. Pour vinegar around the pork. Cover, and cook on Low for 12 hours. Pork should easily pull apart into strands.. Remove pork from the slow cooker and discard any bones. Strain off the liquid, reserving 2 cups (discard any extra). Shred pork using tongs or two forks, and return to the slow cooker.. Stir brown sugar, hot pepper sauce, cayenne pepper, and red pepper flakes into the reserved liquid. Mix into pork in the slow cooker.. Cover and keep on Low setting until serving.

name: BBQ Turkey
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 pound)', 'name': 'whole turkey, neck and giblets removed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken soup base'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'apples, cored and cut into wedges'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'sweet onions, peeled and cut into wedges'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, cut into cubes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'minced garlic, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(750 milliliter) bottle', 'name': 'dry white wine'}
steps: Preheat a gas grill for low heat.. Rub turkey all over with softened butter, inside and out, Repeat with chicken base.. Toss apples, onions, butter cubes, and garlic together in a large bowl. Stuff turkey with apple mixture and place into a disposable aluminum roasting pan. Fold turkey skin around the neck area to cover the hole. Turn turkey over and pour wine into the opening at the other end until turkey is full or the bottle is empty.. Turn turkey so the breast is facing up. Insert a pop-up timer or heat-safe meat thermometer into the breast. Cover the pan loosely with aluminum foil.. Place the roasting pan on the preheated grill and close the lid. Roast until the temperature in the breast reads 170 degrees F (75 degrees C) and the temperature in the thickest part of the thigh reads 180 degrees C (80 degrees C), about 4 hours depending on the temperature of your grill.. Just before turkey reaches the correct temperature, remove the aluminum foil so it can brown during the final minutes of cooking. If it starts to brown too much, replace the foil.. Remove from the grill and let rest for at least 20 minutes before carving.

name: Marinated Grilled Shrimp
ingredients: {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'red wine vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'fresh shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'skewers'}
steps: Stir together olive oil, tomato sauce, garlic, and red wine vinegar in a large bowl. Season with basil, salt, and cayenne pepper.. Add shrimp to the bowl; stir until evenly coated. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes to 1 hour, stirring once or twice.. Preheat the grill to medium heat. Lightly oil the grate.. Thread shrimp onto skewers, piercing once near the tail and once near the head. Discard marinade.. Cook shrimp on the preheated grill until opaque, 2 to 3 minutes per side.. Serve hot and enjoy!

name: Grilled Jalapeño Poppers
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': None, 'name': 'whole jalapeño peppers with stems'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon, cut in half crosswise'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate.. Mix together cream cheese, Cheddar, Parmesan, and garlic powder in a bowl until the mixture is thoroughly blended.. Lay jalapeño pepper on a work surface and cut a lengthwise sliver from the side of the pepper, exposing seeds and white membrane. With the handle of a teaspoon, scrape out seeds and membrane, leaving the hollow pepper. Repeat for the rest of the peppers.. Chop up pepper slivers and mix into cheese stuffing. Stuff each pepper with cheese mixture and wrap each stuffed pepper in a half bacon slice. Secure with toothpicks.. Grill stuffed jalapeños on a less-hot part of the grill until peppers are hot and juicy and bacon is browned, 30 to 40 minutes.

name: Simple Country Ribs
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'pork spareribs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(18 ounce) bottles', 'name': 'barbeque sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, quartered'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}
steps: Place spareribs in a large stockpot; add barbeque sauce, onion, salt, and pepper. Pour in enough water to cover the ribs. Bring to a low boil and simmer for 40 minutes.. Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Transfer spareribs onto the preheated grill, reserving the cooking liquid. Cook, basting with reserved cooking liquid often and turning frequently, until nicely browned, about 20 minutes.

name: Grilled Bacon Jalapeño Wraps
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'fresh jalapeno peppers, halved lengthwise and seeded'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '', 'name': 'toothpicks, soaked in water (Optional)'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Spread cream cheese in each jalapeño half; wrap with bacon. Secure with a toothpick if needed.. Cook on the preheated grill until bacon is crispy, turning often, about 10 minutes.

name: Chocolate Popcorn
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'nonstick cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'quarts', 'name': 'popped popcorn'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanuts (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 250 degrees F (120 degrees C). Spray a 10x15-inch baking pan with nonstick spray. Place popcorn and peanuts into a large metal bowl; set aside.. Combine sugar, butter, corn syrup, and cocoa together in a saucepan over medium-high heat; bring to a boil, stirring continuously, and cook for 2 minutes. Stir in vanilla, then pour over popcorn in the bowl. Stir until popcorn is well-coated; spread on the prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven, stirring several times, for 30 minutes.. Remove popcorn from the oven; allow to cool to room temperature to crisp up. Break into small clumps and store in an airtight container.

name: Apple Squares
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sifted all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2 ¼', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped apple'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped walnuts'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9-inch square pan.. Sift flour, baking powder, salt, and 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon into a medium bowl. Stir 2 tablespoons white sugar and remaining 2 teaspoons cinnamon together in a small bowl.. Mix brown sugar, 1/2 cup white sugar, and melted butter together in a large bowl with a wooden spoon until smooth. Stir in egg and vanilla. Blend in flour mixture until just combined, then stir in apple and walnuts. Spread mixture evenly into the prepared pan and sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture over top.. Bake in the preheated oven until the top springs back when lightly pressed, 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool completely in the pan before cutting into 16 squares.

name: Chinese Pork Chops
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'boneless pork chops'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Pierce pork chops on both sides with a fork.. Whisk soy sauce, brown sugar, lemon juice, oil, ginger, and garlic powder together in a bowl.. Reserve about 1/4 cup marinade for basting; pour remaining marinage into a resealable plastic bag. Add pork chops to the bag, coat with marinade, squeeze out excess air, and seal the bag. Marinate in the refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.. When ready to cook, preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate. Remove pork chops from marinade and shake off excess. Discard remaining marinade.. Cook pork chops on the preheated grill, basting often with the reserved marinade, until no longer pink in the center, 6 to 8 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read 145 degrees F (63 degrees C).

name: Outrageous Warm Chicken Nacho Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 pound) loaf', 'name': 'processed cheese food (such as Velveeta), cubed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes with green chile peppers (such as RO*TEL), drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'cooked skinless, boneless chicken breast halves, shredded'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced green onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'minced jalapeno pepper, or to taste (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'black beans, rinsed and drained'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Stir processed cheese food, diced tomatoes with chiles, shredded cooked chicken, sour cream, green onion, jalapeño, and taco seasoning together in a slow cooker.. Cover and cook on High, stirring occasionally, until cheese has melted and dip is hot, 1 to 2 hours.. Stir in black beans and cook until heated through, 15 minutes.. Serve with chips.

name: Slow Cooker Beer Pulled Pork
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5 pound)', 'name': 'pork butt roast'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 fluid ounce) can', 'name': 'beer (such as Shiner® Bock)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) bottle', 'name': "barbecue sauce (such as Sweet Baby Ray's®)"}
steps: Place pork into the slow cooker. Season with salt, pepper, onion powder, and garlic powder. Pour beer into the bottom of the slow cooker. Cover and cook on High for 1 hour. Reduce the heat to Low and cook until meat is tender and can be easily pulled apart with a fork, 8 to 10 hours.. Remove pork from the slow cooker and shred with two forks. Discard cooking juices. Return shredded pork to the slow cooker and stir in barbecue sauce. Cover and cook on Medium for 1 hour.

name: Favorite Barbecue Chicken
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast halves'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; sauté until tender, about 2 minutes. Stir in ketchup, honey, brown sugar, apple cider vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, and pepper; simmer until sauce has thickened slightly, about 1 or 2 minutes. Remove from heat; set aside to cool slightly.. Dip chicken in sauce to coat on both sides; reserve remaining sauce in the skillet. Transfer chicken onto the preheated grill and cook, turning once, until nicely browned on all sides, about 10 to 15 minutes.. Return chicken to the skillet with sauce; simmer over medium heat until sticky, about 5 minutes on each side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).

name: Quick Baby Back Ribs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mesquite chips, soaked'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(2 pound) slab', 'name': 'baby back pork ribs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Hungarian paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ancho chile powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground thyme'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'barbeque sauce'}
steps: Prepare an outdoor grill for indirect heat with a pile of charcoal on one side and nothing under the food. Once it is going, spread soaked mesquite woodchips on top of charcoal embers.. Remove membrane from ribs. Combine salt, pepper, paprika, chile powder, and thyme in a small bowl; rub into ribs. Cut the slab of ribs in half.. Place ribs over indirect heat; close the lid. Cook for 20 minutes, then brush ribs with barbeque sauce. Cover and continue cooking for 30 more minutes.

name: Baked Buffalo Chicken Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'diced cooked rotisserie chicken'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) packages', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "hot pepper sauce (such as Frank's RedHot)"}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded pepper Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'blue cheese dressing'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'crumbled blue cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'seafood seasoning (such as Old Bay)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pinches', 'name': 'cayenne pepper, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'shredded pepper Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'thinly sliced green onions (Optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Stir chicken, cream cheese, hot pepper sauce, 1/2 cup pepper Jack, blue cheese dressing, blue cheese, seafood seasoning, and a pinch cayenne pepper together in a large bowl until well combined. Transfer to a 9-inch round baking dish and smooth into an even layer. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons pepper Jack over top.. Bake in the preheated oven until lightly browned on top, 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from the oven, add another pinch cayenne pepper, and sprinkle green onions over top.

name: Cajun Deep-Fried Turkey
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '7', 'unit': 'fluid ounces', 'name': 'beer'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion juice'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'garlic juice'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Louisiana-style hot sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 pound)', 'name': 'whole turkey, neck and giblets removed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'gallons', 'name': 'peanut oil for frying, or as needed'}
steps: Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add beer, onion juice, garlic juice, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, black pepper, and cayenne pepper. Mix until marinade is well blended.. Use a marinade-injecting syringe or turkey baster with an injector tip to inject marinade into turkey, including legs, back, wings, thighs, and breasts. Place turkey in a large plastic bag and marinate in the refrigerator, 8 hours to overnight.. When it's time to fry, remove turkey from the bag and place into the cooking basket. Measure the amount of oil needed by lowering turkey into the fryer and filling with enough oil to cover it. Remove turkey and set aside.. Heat oil to 365 degrees F (185 degrees C). Return turkey to the cooking basket and lower slowly into hot oil using the hanging device that comes with turkey deep-fryers. The turkey should be completely submerged in hot oil. Cook for 36 minutes or 3 minutes per pound of turkey. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the thickest part of thigh should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Turn off the flame and slowly remove turkey from oil, making sure all of the oil drains out of the cavity. Allow turkey to rest on a serving platter before carving, about 20 minutes.

name: Grilled Delmonico Steaks
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'steak seasoning'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'steak sauce (e.g. A-1)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'crushed dried rosemary'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, roughly chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(10 ounce)', 'name': 'Delmonico (rib-eye) steaks'}
steps: Combine oil, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, steak seasoning, steak sauce, salt, pepper, and rosemary in the bowl of a food processor. Add garlic and onion; process until well blended.. Prick steaks on both sides with a fork, then place into a large glass baking dish. Pour marinade over steaks, and flip steaks several times to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours, or overnight.. When ready to cook, preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate.. Remove steaks from marinade and shake off excess. Discard remaining marinade.. Place steaks on the preheated grill; cover and cook until beginning to firm and are hot and slightly pink in the center, about 10 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read 140 degrees F (60 degrees C) for medium.

name: Deep-Fried Mushrooms
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'oil for frying, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'button mushrooms, quartered'}
steps: Stir flour and garlic salt together in a medium bowl. Mix in water and egg until smooth.. Heat oil in a large deep skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of batter will sizzle and float to the top.. Working in small batches, dip mushrooms into batter and fry in hot oil until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.

name: Slow Roasted BBQ Beef Roast
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Spanish paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried rosemary'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless rump roast'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, sliced'}
steps: Prepare an outdoor rotisserie grill for medium heat.. Mix paprika, salt, pepper, rosemary, and thyme together in a small bowl.. Cut slits on all sides of roast; insert garlic into slits. Rub spice mixture all over meat.. Place roast on the preheated rotisserie and cook until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center reads at least 145 degrees F (63 degrees C), 2 to 5 hours. Let rest for 20 minutes before slicing.

name: Slider-Style Mini Burgers
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1.25 ounce) envelope', 'name': 'onion soup mix'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '24', 'unit': '', 'name': 'dinner rolls, split'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced pickles (Optional)'}
steps: Gather the ingredients.. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Cover a baking sheet with aluminum foil and grease with cooking spray. Grease a sheet of aluminum foil; set aside.. Mix together ground beef and onion soup mix in a large skillet; cook and stir over medium-high heat until beef is crumbly and evenly browned, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain and discard any excess grease.. Remove the skillet from heat; stir in Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise.. Place roll bottoms on the prepared baking sheet. Spread beef mixture onto each bottom. Cover with tops. Cover sandwiches with the prepared sheet of aluminum foil.. Bake in the preheated oven until burgers are heated through and cheese is melted, about 30 minutes.. Serve with sliced pickles and enjoy!

name: Buffalo Chicken Wraps
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breasts, cut into bite-size pieces'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'hot sauce'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(10 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded lettuce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'celery stalk, diced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'blue cheese dressing'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Heat oil and butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat until butter melts. Add chicken; cook and stir until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, about 10 minutes. Remove from the heat.. Pour hot sauce into the skillet and toss until chicken is coated.. Lay tortillas out on a work surface. Divide sauced chicken evenly among tortillas.. Top the chicken with lettuce and celery, then drizzle blue cheese dressing over top.. Fold in tortilla sides and roll around filling. Serve and enjoy!

name: Loaded Tater Tots
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(32 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen bite-size potato nuggets (such as Tater Tots)'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'shallot, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'whole milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sour cream (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded sharp Cheddar cheese, divided'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sour cream, or to taste (Optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Spread potato nuggets in a single layer on a baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until lightly golden, 20 to 25 minutes.. Meanwhile, heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook bacon in the hot skillet, turning occasionally, until evenly browned, about 10 minutes. Drain bacon on a paper towel-lined plate, then chop coarsely and set aside.. Make sauce: Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Cook and stir shallot in hot butter until fragrant. Stir in flour and cook until light golden, about 2 minutes. Whisk in milk and sour cream; stir until smooth and thick, about 5 minutes. Season with black pepper and nutmeg. Stir in 1 cup Cheddar cheese until fully melted.. Transfer potato nuggets to a 9x13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle bacon on top. Pour cheese sauce over nuggets. Cover with remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.. Bake in the preheated oven just until cheese melts, about 7 minutes. Garnish with green onions and sour cream to serve.

name: Emily's Chipotle Chili
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'bulk hot Italian sausage'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'kidney beans (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'minced chipotle peppers in adobo sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato paste'}
steps: Cook sausage and ground beef in a large pot over medium-high heat until lightly browned and crumbly; drain. Add chili powder, cumin, and coriander; cook and stir for 1 minute until fragrant. Stir in garlic and onion; cook and stir until onion has softened and turned translucent, about 4 minutes.. Stir in diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, kidney beans, chipotle peppers, salt, and pepper. Bring to a simmer, then transfer chili into a slow cooker. Cover, and cook on Low for 8 to 10 hours. Stir in tomato paste an hour before chili is done.

name: Grilled Lobster Tails
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10 ounce)', 'name': 'rock lobster tails'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat the grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Pour lemon juice into a small bowl; slowly whisk in olive oil. Whisk in salt, paprika, white pepper, and garlic powder until combined.. Split lobster tails lengthwise with a large knife, then brush flesh with some marinade.. Place lobster tails flesh-side down on the preheated grill and cook, turning once and basting frequently with marinade, until opaque and firm to the touch, 10 to 12 minutes. Discard any remaining marinade.

name: Ranch Burgers
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'lean ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'crushed saltine crackers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'ranch dressing mix'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Mix ground beef, onion, crushed crackers, egg, and ranch dressing mix together in a bowl until well combined. Form into eight hamburger patties.. Cook patties on the preheated grill until no longer pink in the center, about 5 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 160 degrees F (70 degrees C).

name: Southern-Style Egg Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sweet India pickle relish'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'yellow mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'dashes', 'name': 'hot sauce (such as Tabasco®) (Optional)'}
steps: Cover eggs with water in a saucepan, bring to a low boil, let boil slowly for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.. Transfer eggs to ice water to chill for 5 minutes; peel. Grate eggs into a medium mixing bowl and add mayonnaise, relish, mustard, sugar, lemon juice, salt, pepper, and hot sauce. Mix well.. Chill in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.

name: Hash Brown Casserole for the Slow Cooker
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded processed cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed cream of mushroom soup, undiluted'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(32 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen hash brown potatoes, thawed'}
steps: Combine sour cream, processed cheese, cream of mushroom soup, onion, salt, and black pepper. Gradually stir in hash browns until evenly coated.. Coat inside of a slow cooker with cooking spray or butter. Add hash brown mixture to slow cooker. Cover, and cook on High for 1 1/2 hours, then reduce heat to Low, and cook for 2 1/2 hours more.

name: Blueberry Crumb Bars
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground cinnamon (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter or shortening'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fresh blueberries'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'cornstarch'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch pan.. Stir flour, 1 cup sugar, and baking powder together in a medium bowl; mix in salt and cinnamon, if desired. Use a fork or pastry cutter to blend in butter and egg. Dough will be crumbly. Pat half of dough into the prepared pan.. Stir 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch together in another bowl; gently mix in blueberries. Sprinkle blueberry mixture evenly over prepared crust. Crumble remaining dough over berry layer.. Bake in the preheated oven until top is slightly brown, about 45 minutes. Cool completely before cutting into squares.

name: White Texas Sheet Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'almond extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '4 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': "confectioners' sugar"}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'almond extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}
steps: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. In a large saucepan, bring 1 cup butter and water to a boil. Remove from heat, and stir in flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, 1 teaspoon almond extract, salt, and baking soda until smooth. Pour batter into a greased 10x15-inch baking pan.. Bake in the preheated oven for 20 to 22 minutes, or until cake is golden brown and tests done. Cool for 20 minutes.. Combine 1/2 cup butter and milk in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Mix in sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract. Stir in pecans. Spread frosting over warm cake.

name: Cedar Plank Salmon
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried dill weed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(6 ounce)', 'name': 'salmon fillets, with skin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': '12-inch untreated cedar plank, soaked in water for 2 hours'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C).. Combine brown sugar, sesame oil, sesame seeds, and dill in a small bowl. Mix in water, a little at a time, adding just enough to make the mixture liquid. Stir in soy sauce and pepper.. Place salmon fillets, skin-side down, onto the soaked cedar plank. Spoon sugar mixture evenly over fillets to fully coat.. Place cedar plank directly on a rack in the preheated oven; bake until fish flakes easily with a fork, 30 to 40 minutes.

name: Best Football Dip Ever
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) jar', 'name': 'prepared salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 pound) loaf', 'name': 'processed cheese food, sliced'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Place the ground beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring to crumble, until no longer pink. Drain off grease.. Spread the cream cheese in an even layer in the bottom of a 9 inch square baking dish. Spread a layer of salsa over the cream cheese, then cover with a layer of ground beef. Top with slices of processed cheese and cover the dish with aluminum foil.. Bake for 15 minutes in the preheated oven, or until heated through. Serve hot.

name: Milly's Oatmeal Brownies
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup unsalted', 'name': 'butter, room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'firmly packed light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 9x13-inch baking pan.. Beat butter, brown sugar, and white sugar together in a large bowl until thoroughly combined and creamy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Stir in vanilla extract until combined. Stir in rolled oats, flour, chocolate chips, raisins, walnuts, baking soda, baking powder, and salt until all ingredients moistened; spread into the prepared baking pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool in the pan for about 5 minutes before cutting into bars.

name: Grilled Soy-Sesame Asparagus
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'toasted sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'fresh asparagus, trimmed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'toasted sesame seeds'}
steps: Preheat grill for high heat.. In a bowl, mix sesame oil, soy sauce, garlic, and brown sugar. Place asparagus in the bowl, and toss to coat.. Lightly oil a fine-mesh grill grate. Place asparagus on grate, and cook 8 minutes, until tender but firm. Garnish with sesame seeds to serve.

name: Grilled Teriyaki Tuna
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'teriyaki sauce'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(4 ounce) fillets', 'name': 'yellowfin tuna'}
steps: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the teriyaki sauce, oil, garlic, and pepper. Place the tuna fillets in the bag. Seal the bag with as little air in it as possible. Give the mix a good shake, to ensure the tuna fillets are well coated. Marinate for 30 minutes in the refrigerator.. Meanwhile, preheat an outdoor grill for high heat, and lightly oil grate.. Remove tuna from marinade, and place on grill. For rare tuna, grill for 3 to 5 minutes on each side. For medium, grill 5 to 8 minutes per side. For well done, grill for 8 to 10 minutes per side.

name: Sassy Tailgate Sandwiches
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 count) package', 'name': 'Hawaiian bread rolls'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'shaved Black Forest ham'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'Gruyere cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) tub', 'name': 'PHILADELPHIA Chive & Onion Cream Cheese Spread'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried minced onion'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Cut all rolls in half. Place roll bottoms in 9x13-inch pan.. Place equal amounts of ham on each roll bottom. Top with Gruyere.. On each of the roll tops, spread a generous amount of the cream cheese spread. Return the tops to the bottoms making sandwiches.. In a separate bowl, mix together the butter, Worcestershire sauce, onion and Parmesan cheese. Pour over your sandwiches and let sit for at least 20 minutes. (You can make these ahead of time and allow to sit in fridge overnight.). Place sandwiches, covered in foil, in a preheated 350 degrees F oven. Bake for 20 minutes or until warmed through. Enjoy!

name: Juicy Lucy Burgers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic salt'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'American cheese (such as Kraft)'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'hamburger buns, split'}
steps: Mix ground beef, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, and garlic salt together in a bowl until well combined. Form into eight thin patties, each slightly larger than a cheese slice.. Stack all cheese slices and cut into four squares. Place one small cheese stack in the center of a beef patty; cover with another beef patty and tightly pinch the edges together to seal around the cheese. Be sure to seal tightly, or the cheese will burst through when cooked. Repeat with the remaining cheese and patties.. Heat a large cast-iron skillet over medium heat. Cook patties in the hot skillet until well browned, about 4 minutes; they will puff up due to steam from the melting cheese. Flip patties, prick the tops to release steam, and cook until browned on the other side and no longer pink in the center; about 4 more minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 160 degrees F (70 degrees C).. Serve on hamburger buns.

name: Horseshoe
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(9 ounce) bag', 'name': 'frozen french fries'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bread, toasted'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'half-and-half'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'hot sauce to taste'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Spread french fries out on a baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes in the preheated oven, or until golden brown.. Meanwhile, divide the ground beef into four equal parts and form into patties. Fry the patties in a large skillet over medium-high heat until well done, about 4 minutes per side.. Melt the butter in a saucepan over medium heat and whisk in the flour. Cook while stirring constantly for 4 minutes to cook out the flavor of raw flour. Gradually whisk in the half-and-half so that no lumps form. Bring to a simmer then remove from the heat and add the cheese; stir until melted. Season with salt, pepper, and hot sauce to taste.. Place 2 slices of toasted bread onto 2 dinner plates and top each slice with a hamburger patty. Top each patty with cooked french fries. Pour the cheese sauce on top of everything and serve immediately.

name: Grilled Chicken Spiedies
ingredients: {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine vinegar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'freshly squeezed lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh mint leaves'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried basil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless skinless chicken thighs, cut into 3 pieces'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'skewers'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Italian-style hoagie buns'}
steps: Combine vinegar, olive oil, lemon juice, mint, garlic, sugar, oregano, basil, salt, red pepper flakes, and black pepper in a blender. Puree until liquefied, about 30 seconds.. Place chicken thighs in a large resealable plastic bag, pour in marinade and massage to coat. Squeeze out excess air and seal the bag. Marinate in the refrigerator for 24 hours, turning occasionally.. Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Remove chicken and place on the skewers. Season with salt. Pour the marinade into a small saucepan. Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced slightly, about 2 minutes.. Place skewers on the preheated grill and cook for 5 to 6 minutes, turn and cook until the chicken is no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, 5 to 6 more minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Remove from grill and rest the meat for a few minutes.. Toast hoagie rolls and spread each with some of the reserved marinade. Place a skewer on each roll and carefully remove the skewer, leaving the chicken in the bun.

name: Barbeque Halibut Steaks
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 pound)', 'name': 'halibut steak'}
steps: Preheat grill for medium-high heat.. Place butter, brown sugar, garlic, lemon juice, soy sauce, and pepper in a small saucepan. Warm over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar is completely dissolved.. Lightly oil grill grate. Brush fish with brown sugar sauce, and place on grill. Cook for 5 minutes per side, or until fish can be easily flaked with a fork, basting with sauce. Discard remaining basting sauce.
